            <pb facs="#TL-0602.jpg" n="part4_p128.jpg" xml:id="img_0128" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part4_p128.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_128_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>[597]
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>tendency in Prussian militarism to glorify war, not to see that it is in itself an expression of the
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/><rs type="keyword" ref="#Demonic">demonic</rs> possession of mankind as a whole, but to call it a glorious thing in itself. Now of course
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>every evil can produce virtues which otherwise never would come into existence, as diseases often
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>do to people. But a disease is a disease even if has a wholesome effect on a special person. And so,
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>war is EVIL, even if it produces [something] which can be considered as good.
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>Now let’s look at the second type, the legalistic. It says: ''If this is true, if the <rs type="keyword" ref="#Kingdom_of_God">kingdom
               <lb break="no" facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>of God </rs>implies the universal peace, because everything is rooted in the same eternal ground, then
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>let’s try to do that, and everybody MUST be a pacifist, and everybody must REFUSE to go to
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>war.'' This legalistic form of <rs type="keyword" ref="#Pacifism">pacifism</rs> ALSO overlooks the separation of essence and existence.
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>It doesn’t see that under the conditions of existence, of human <rs type="keyword" ref="#Estrangement">estrangement</rs>, estrangement of
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>everything FROM everything and from ITSELF, the <rs type="keyword" ref="#Power">power</rs> which is the <rs type="keyword" ref="#Structure_of_reality">structure of reality</rs>--
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/><rs type="keyword" ref="#God">God</rs> Himself is <rs type="keyword" ref="#Ultimacy">ultimate</rs> power--actualizes itself in terms of compulsion, through force. This is
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_14" n="N014"/>the situation which we have in [the] inner-political realm--without the inner application, or
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_15" n="N015"/>at least the threat of force, no <community>community</community>, even the smallest, could exist. And we have it in
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_16" n="N016"/>relation of the great groups to each other. This is man's <rs type="keyword" ref="#Predicament">predicament</rs>, and it is impossible to deny it.
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_17" n="N017"/>But then there is a third consideration, namely the consideration that IF the idea of
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_18" n="N018"/>the <rs type="keyword" ref="#Kingdom_of_God">kingdom of Go</rs>d is the universal unity, and IF there are saving powers in existence so that
               <lb facs="#facs_128_tr_1_tl_19" n="N019"/>existence is not thoroughly self-destructive, then these saving powers should work, and one should
            </p>
            
